# Fix Login Failure (ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED)

The user is experiencing a login failure because the backend is unresponsive on port 5000 and has incorrect CORS/Frontend IP configurations in `.env`.

## Proposed Changes

### [Server]

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/.env)
- Update `FRONTEND_URL` and `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` to use the correct machine IP `10.172.19.161` (currently truncated to `10.172.19.16`).
- Change `NODE_ENV` to `development` for better debugging.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `curl -i http://localhost:5000/api/health` to ensure the server is responding.

### Manual Verification
- Ask the user to try logging in again at `http://10.172.19.161:8080/login`.
